      "body" : "No, we will not use HTML in the bitcoin core client. It might look unusual but that is small fries compared with the security issues with interfacing with a browser, or (snicker) integrating one.\r\n\r\nAllowing GET requests to post JSON-RPC requests is a violation of the standard use of http methods. GET should never change state. However you can pass `-rest` option to be able to use a  (read-only, stateless) subset of the API through GET.",
